<Content>The good and the bad! - 3 night stay in April After a terrible travel day - arriving 4 1/2 hours later than expected we made it to the hotel around 7pm on a Thursday. Lobby looks nice - check in went fairly smooth. Got to the room and it was warm but figured we came from cold to warm climate and maybe they had not turned up air. Did a little unpacking - went to the dinner buffet at hotel (was ok but not great) - did a little walking around beach - back to room. Room still warm but so tired we go to bed - wait up soaking wet from sweat around 2am- no air - and room is an oven. Call down to front desk - they send up a security guard that was no help. Next day had to wait till 9:30 am to see a manager - No other rooms available - but manager was very nice - said they would take care of us - to check back later - they tried to fix air but were not able to. So we got another room - on same floor - much better room - with balcony facing pool and ocean (other room had no balcony and view of building next door!) They also sent us a bottle of champagne and some fruit that night. Alot of construction going on in hotel - alot of workers taking elevators - very dirty - very slow elevators! Location was ok - nice boardwalk to walk along beach area. Can follow this to another walkway all the way to almost end of South beach area. It's a long long walk but very pleasant.Pool area was nice also - small pool but nicely setup. Bartenders at pool bar very slow - but we had sandwiches there and they where good and prices where reasonable.Would go to Miami again but would probably stay closer to South Beach where all the shops/restaurants are.Lincoln rd(ave?) was worth a visit - great shops - alot of nice places to eat - had dinner at outside restaurant - be careful - girl had purse stolen from her - she didn't notice someone had taken it when she had left it by her leg when sitting at table. 
